==Old English==
===Etymology 1===
From Germanic ''*juk-'', from Indo-European ''*i̯ugom''.  Cognate with Old Saxon ''[[juc]]'' (Dutch ''[[juk]]''), Old High German ''[[joh]]'' (German ''[[Joch]]''), Old Norse ''[[ok]]'' (Swedish ''[[ok]]''), Gothic [[𐌾𐌿𐌺]].  The Indo-European root is also the source of Vedic Sanskrit [[युगम्]], Greek ''[[ζυγόν]]'', Latin ''[[iugum]]'', Old Church Slavonic ''[[иго]]'' (Polish ''[[igo]]''), Lithuanian ''[[jungti|jùngti]]'', Welsh ''[[iau]]''.

